{
  "mos_rules": "# 3. Gang Relations Guide\nAllied Gangs:\n```\n| - 1. Allied gangs are basically people from other gangs Who will help us in wars, They wont kill us and We wont kill them in return, Basically meaning The 2 gangs which is us and that gang becomes best friends.. MEANING, No one from any allied gang or you should kill each-other, This is basically our brotherin right here.\n```\nAllied Players:\n```\n| - 2. Allied Players are a whole different thing, This means if someone is chill With MOS [A member of our gang], They go on the \"Neutral Players\" List, This means they cant kill you. And you cant kill them.\n```\nNeutral Gangs:\n```\n| - 3. Neutral gangs are basically other gangs in Valley Prison we are chill with meaning The leaders of MOS And that gang is chill, The members of MOS And that gang is chill with each-other And we just have a neutral relationship bond with them. However, if they kill an MOS Member or try to attack you or a member Or an ally you are given permission to defend yourself or the friendly From that 'chilled' gang member and you should report it to Us So We Can talk to the leaders of the gangs involved and work it out. However, This may lead to the neutral gang becoming one of our opps if they do tend to do such a stupid act.\n```\nOpp Gangs:\n```\n| - 4. Opp Gangs and KOS Players list..\nDo NOT hold back, Kill people who are in the \"Opp gangs\" ON SIGHT, And kill KOS Players on sight too, These are basically the Nazis we gotta fight, They will, show no mercy.. and neither will we.\n```\n-# These rules are related to -->  https://discord.com/channels/1471662897397633034/1471663466569011242 and https://discord.com/channels/1471662897397633034/1471663476400193628\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------",
  "vprp_rules": "**The following rules draw upon DISCORD and ROBLOX TOS therefore, apply to any channel or voice chat. Attempting to bypass or find loopholes to avoid following the said guidelines will result in punishment depending on the severity of the guideline you violated.**\n\n*If you'd like to get a more in-depth explanation of each rule, please refer to the \"Information\" Channel.*\n\n---\n\n# 📜 IN-SERVER GUIDELINES\n\n**Respect** | Regardless of rank, everyone must be treated with equal respect. There will be no bias against or for anyone within the community.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, but if taken to the extreme, it can result in a temporary ban.\n\n**Disrupting Conversations** | Disturbing conversations would include Spamming or Flooding within the chats, which can be frustrating or annoying for members within the server.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, but if taken to the extreme, it can result in a temporary ban.\n➢ This can include using \"#\" to make your messages larger.\n\n**Profanity** | Swearing and Profanity are allowed within the Discord Server, although it must be kept to a minimum. Discriminatory remarks are prohibited.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, but if taken to the extreme, it can result in a temporary ban.\n\n**Advertising & Promoting Content** | Sharing content to promote your or others' videos, games, discord servers, ETC, can be punishable. Especially when this \"Content\" is NSFW related.\n➢ Depending on the severity of the content that is shared, it can be a minor offense to a major offense, resulting in a permanent ban.\n\n**Malicious Intentions** | This includes things such as Threats, and DOXXING, DDoSSING, or SCAMMING. All are strictly prohibited. As for threats, there are 2 types. Indirect and Direct threats, it doesn't matter if the threat is either; they're both still considered threats.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments can range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**Languages** | We are an English-only speaking server; we do not allow other languages to be spoken due to Language barriers.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, but if taken to the extreme, it can result in a temporary ban. This is the case because of the content of the messages sent. As it can be discriminatory or NSFW.\n\n**Discrimination** | This is the mistreatment of a person due to their race, sexuality, disability, political ideology, or religion. This is incredibly disrespectful and not tolerated.\n➢ This is a major offense, with punishments usually ranging from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**Harassment** | There are many types of harassment; all are inappropriate and disgusting behavior.\n➢ Most harassment cases will go to IA; anything else, such as member-on-member harassment, will be left to staff. Only if the case involves Staff Members, Supervisors+ will handle it from there. If it involves a Supervisor, there will be times when another supervisor will handle it or a Staff Manager.\n\n**Bypassing** | There of course are words or content that are automated, although members can still find ways to bypass this. This, of course, is punishable.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments can range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**NSFW Topics/Content** | NSFW stands for \"Not Safe For Work\", content that is violent or sexual. Strictly prohibited.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments can range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n➢ Any sexual content, harassment, coercion, blackmail or other illegal acts towards minors will result in a permanent ban and report to Discord. This not tolerated, and there will be punishments.\n➢ All interactions must follow the Discord TOS\n\n**Controversial Topics** | These can be topics that are related to politics, religion, disabilities, or sexuality/gender Identity. Things that not everyone can agree on, and will start drama within the server.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments can range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**Channel Misuse** | Although this is a light offense, it's still not acceptable. Use chats as they're meant to be used.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, usually only a mute to a kick from the server.\n\n**\"Mini-Modding\"** | If they don't have any staff role, they do not have the authority to moderate other people within the Discord.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, although if taken to the extreme can reach a kick.\n\n**Starting/Instigating Drama** | There will be times when conflict will stir up, attempting to have it continue, whether it be by just mentioning in the past vaguely, or blatantly. This can get you in trouble.\n➢ This can be both a minor and major offense if you are intentionally starting drama, and even refuse to disperse, you'll be punished more harshly. If you are seen instigating an argument, you may meet the same fate as those who are arguing.\n\n**Discord TOS** | Follow the Discord TOS\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments usually go straight to a permanent ban.\n\n---\n\n# 🎮 IN-GAME GUIDELINES\n\n**AFK Farming** | Farming for Levels & EXP illegitimately, referring to not playing the game and gaining EXP/Levels.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, unless taken to the extreme with the use of things such as clients or macros. Punishments can be from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Tool Abuse [TA]** | Using tools not for their intended purpose.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense; punishments can be from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Random Killing [RK]** | Purposefully killing players who aren't a threat, (ex. rking those with keycards or any other item that doesn't cause any harm)\n➢ This is considered a minor offense; punishments can be from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Spawn Camping [SC]** | Killing players at their spawn.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense; punishments can be from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Teaming** | Helping other teams to give them an advantage.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense; punishments can be from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Erotic Roleplay [ERP]** | Doing sexual or inappropriate roleplay.\n➢ This is considered a major offense, resulting in a permanent ban.\n\n**Inappropriate Conduct** | NSFW comments, but doesn't include any sexual activities.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments can range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**Back-and-Forth [BAF]** | Back-and-forth movements behind or in front of a player.\n➢ BAF is inherently a minor offense, with punishments ranging from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Toxicity** | Malicious behavior or intent with the use of words or actions.\n➢ This is inherently a minor offense, but if taken to the extreme, it can result in a temporary ban.\n\n**Vote-Kick Abuse [VKA]** | Misusing vote-kicking, kicking a player without a valid reason.\n➢ This is inherently a minor offense, with punishments ranging from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Controversial Topics** | These can be topics that are related to politics, religion, or sexuality/gender Identity. Things that not everyone can agree on, and will start drama within the game.\n➢ This can be both a minor and major offense if you are intentionally attempting to start something with the discussion of these controversial topics.\n\n**Racism & Discrimination** | Mistreatment and disrespectful remarks due to physical appearance, religion, and beliefs, ETC.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments can range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**Exploiting** | Using an external client/script to gain an unfair advantage.\n➢ This will always be a permanent ban.\n\n**Glitch Abuse [GA]** | Abusing in-game bugs or glitches to gain an unfair advantage or to troll other players.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments range from a temporary ban to a permanent ban.\n\n**Duping Items** | Abusing a bug in-game to multiply weapons or other items, in an attempt to lag or give the team an unfair advantage.\n➢ This is inherently a minor offense, unless taken to the extreme, it'll begin start follow the punishments of \"Glitch abuse.\"\n\n**Leaving to Avoid Moderation [LTAM]** | Leaving the game or changing teams while being moderated.\n➢ This is considered a major offense; it will add to your punishment length.\n\n**Interference with Moderation [IWM]** | When Staff are moderating In-Game, there will be times when people will interfere with the moderation of others, to attempt to give the Staff a hard time whilst dealing with another offender.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense unless taken to the extreme; in some cases, you can meet the same fate as the person the moderator is punishing. This can range from a kick to a temporary ban.\n\n**Alternative Accounts [ALT]** | Using alternative accounts, or ALT for short, to avoid an In-Game punishment.\n➢ This will always be a permanent ban. There are some cases where even a confession to doing so will result in a permanent ban as well, leaving you to need to appeal. We cannot for sure if someone is lying unless it is blatantly obvious.\n\n**Offensive/Bypassed Content** | Playing loud, offensive, or copyrighted songs via the radio & VC.\n➢ This can be both a minor and a major offense, depending on the severity of the content that is played.\n\n**Targeting [NLR]** | After you or the other person dies, and intentionally looking to target them.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense, with punishments ranging from a verbal warning to a temporary ban.\n\n**Misuse of Helpcalls [MOH]** | Misusing the \"!mod\" command in-game.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense with punishments ranging from a warning to a temporary ban.\n\n**Avatar Misuse** | Misusing your avatar to appear as another team, in an attempt to confuse, troll, or gain an unfair advantage.\n➢ This is considered a minor offense unless taken to the extreme; punishments can range from a warning to a temporary ban.\n\n**Inappropriate Avatar** | Misusing your avatar to appear as things that are NSFW or controversial.\n➢ This can be both a minor offense and a major offense. It heavily depends on the severity of what you are wearing.\n\n**Roblox TOS** | Follow Roblox TOS\n➢ This is considered a major offense; punishments usually go straight to a permanent ban.",
  "mos_last_updated": "2026-03-02T05:48:05.866703+00:00",
